# Dramaturge — TypeScript Rules

## Project
Agentic exploratory QA engine: TypeScript 5.8, Node ≥ 20, ES modules, pnpm 9, Vitest 4, Playwright + Stagehand.

## Commands
- Build: `pnpm run build`
- Test: `pnpm run test`
- Lint: `pnpm run lint`
- Format: `pnpm run format:check`

## Must Follow
- Named exports only — no default exports
- `.js` extension in all relative imports: `import { X } from './module.js'`
- `import type` for type-only imports
- Semicolons always, single quotes, 2-space indent, 100-char width
- Trailing commas ES5 style
- `const` by default, no `var`, no `any`
- Zod for config validation, discriminated unions for variant types
- Options objects for 3+ parameter functions
- Max 150 lines/function, complexity ≤ 20, depth ≤ 4, params ≤ 5
- Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `perf:`, `ci:`

## Testing
- Co-located: `foo.test.ts` beside `foo.ts`
- `vi.hoisted()` for mock factories, `vi.mock()` with `.js` paths
- `vi.clearAllMocks()` in `beforeEach`
- Factory helpers with `Partial<T>` overrides
- Never remove existing tests

## Error Handling
- Permissive: catch errors, return structured outcomes, don't crash
- Workers: `completed | blocked | timed-out | failed`
